{% from "../macros/example.njk" import example %}

{% set rightExample %}
<z-toggle label="toggle input after label" right></z-toggle>
<z-toggle label="toggle input"></z-toggle>
{% endset %}

{% set labelsExample %}
<z-toggle label="toggle input with custom inside labels" onlabel="ON" offlabel="OFF"></z-toggle>
<z-toggle label="toggle input with custom inside labels" onlabel="✓"></z-toggle>
<z-toggle label="toggle input with custom inside labels" offlabel="✗"></z-toggle>
{% endset %}

{% set disabledExample %}
<z-toggle label="toggle input disabled" disabled></z-toggle>
<z-toggle label="toggle input active & disabled" active disabled></z-toggle>
{% endset %}

{% set changeEventExample %}
<z-toggle id="change-event-toggle" label="Toggle with z-change event"></z-toggle>
<p>Result: <b id="change-event-result">?</b></p>

<script>
    const $toggle = document.querySelector('#change-event-toggle')
    const $result = document.querySelector('#change-event-result')

    $toggle.addEventListener('z-change', ({ detail }) => {
        $result.innerText = detail.value
    })
</script>
{% endset %}

<div class="container">
    <h2>Toggle</h2>

    <p><code>{{ '<z-toggle>' | escape }}</code> is a component that provides the same functionality as a native <code>{{ '<input type="checkbox">' | escape }}</code> enhanced with a better and unified design.</p>
    <div class="notif success">This component has the same api than the <code>{{ '<z-checkbox>' | escape }}</code> with some additional features and a different design.</div>

    {{ example (template='<z-toggle label="toggle input"></z-toggle>', about="Basic toggle") }}
    
    <hr>
    <h3 id="attributes">Attributes</h3>

    <h4 id="attributes-label">Label</h4>

    <p>The <b>label</b> attribute provides a clickable label for the <code>{{ '<z-toggle>' | escape }}</code> component.</p>

    <h4 id="attributes-right">Right</h4>

    <p>The <b>right</b> attribute makes the <code>{{ '<z-toggle>' | escape }}</code> component appear after its label.</p>

    {{ example(template=rightExample, about="toggle input after label") }}

    <h4 id="attributes-active">Active</h4>

    <p>The <b>active</b> attribute is watched and makes the toggle beeing active if provided (no value needed).</p>
    <p>This attribute can also be used for setting a default value to the component.</p>

    {{ example(template='<z-toggle label="toggle input active" active></z-toggle>', about="toggle input active") }}

    <h4 id="attributes-onlabel-offlabel">Onlabel & Offlabel</h4>

    <p>The <b>onlabel</b> and <b>offlabel</b> attributes add little labels inside the <code>{{ '<z-toggle>' | escape }}</code> component.</p>

    <div class="alert warn">
        Only 3 letters of the labels will usualy be visible.
    </div>

    <div class="alert success">
        You can use unicode symbols as inside labels.
    </div>

    {{ example(template=labelsExample, about="toggle input with custom inside labels") }}

    <h4 id="attributes-disabled">Disabled</h4>

    <p>The <b>disabled</b> attribute prevents the toggle from beeing used and gives it an understandable styling.</p>

    {{ example(template=disabledExample, about="toggle input disabled") }}

    <hr>
    <h3 id="accessibility">Accessibility</h3>

    <p>The <code>{{ '<z-toggle>' | escape }}</code> component works with the native <code>{{ '<input type="checkbox">' | escape }}</code> element to provide an accessible experience.</p>

    <hr>
    <h3 id="events">Events</h3>

    <h4 id="events-change">z-change</h4>

    <p>The <b>z-change</b> event is fired whenever the value of the toggle changes. It is a <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/CustomEvent/CustomEvent">CustomEvent</a>.</p>

    <p>This event provides a <b>detail</b> object containing the new value of the toggle.</p>

    {{ example(template=changeEventExample, about="z-change event") }}
</div>
